They are blueprints to Objects

Class is instantiated with new keyword

Class helps in inheritance

Example:
    class Person {
        constructor() {
            this.name = 'Venki';
        }
        printName() {
            console.log(this.name);
        }
    }

    const person = new Person();
    person.printName();  // prints 'Venki'

    class Human {
        constructor() {
            this.gender = "male";
        }
        printGender() {
            console.log(this.gender);
        }
    }

 class Person extends Human {
        constructor() {
            super();   // to initialise the parent class Human
            this.name = 'Venki';
        }
        printName() {
            console.log(this.name);
        }
    }

    const person = new Person();
    person.printGender(); // prints "male"

    +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
    ** Properties are variables attached to Class/ Objects
    ** Methods are functions attached to Class / Objects